Census Tracts, 2016

Source: R/stl_sf_tracts.R
stl_sf_tracts.Rd

A simple features data set containing the geometry and associated attributes for the 2016 City of St. Louis census tracts.

data(stl_sf_tracts)

Format

A data frame with 106 rows and 13 variables:

STATEFP

state FIPS code

COUNTYFP

county FIPS code

TRACTCE

tract FIPS code

GEOID

full GEOID string

NAME

tract FIPS code, decimal

NAMELSAD

tract name

MTFCC

geographic object classification

FUNCSTAT

current functional status

ALAND

area of tract land, square meters

AWATER

area of tract water, square meters

INTPTLAT

interpolated centroid value, latitude

INTPTLON

interpolated centroid value, longitude

geometry

simple features geometry

Source

U.S. Census Bureau

#' @examples str(stl_sf_tracts) head(stl_sf_tracts) summary(stl_sf_tracts$ALAND)
